      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add <strong>half</strong> your<strong> cornflour </strong>(save the rest for later!) and<strong> </strong>2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour </strong>to a plate, season with a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and a generous grind of<strong> black pepper </strong>and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>flour mix</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>chicken thighs</strong> to the <strong>flour mix</strong>, then press firmly into the mixture,<strong> </strong>making sure to evenly coat them on both sides – this is your <strong>coated chicken</strong></p>",
