    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>cornflour</strong> in a bowl with 125ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[190ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>tomato</strong> <strong>ketchup </strong>and<strong> soy</strong> <strong>sauce </strong>with your <strong>rice</strong> <strong>vinegar</strong>, <strong>ginger</strong> <strong>&</strong> <strong>garlic</strong> <strong>paste </strong>and 2 tsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [3 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> and mix it all together – this is your <strong>sweet & sour sauce</strong></p><p>Trim and chop your <strong>spring onion[s]</strong> in half, then cut lengthways into thin strips</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
